Barry Seal was one of the most prolific pilots for Pablo. He sometimes did work for the CIA and used Louisiana as his smuggling entry point. After turning state's evidence, threatening to reveal how Pablo was connected to the Nicaraguan government...and the CIA...he was murked outside a Baton Rouge salvation Army where he was forced to live while on work release. The Colombians who did the deed are still in Angola state Prison today.
George Jung partnered with Carlos Lehder to turn the Caribbean into the 1st primary transshipment station. Also a pilot, he spent much of his later adult life in federal prison and recently died.
Fabio Ochoa, one member of the most important family ever in the Coke business, is the only one to suffer significant prison time- he is currently finishing a 30 year term in US federal prison.
Griselda Blanco. One of many major major distributors for the Colombian bosses based in the U.S. Her penchant for violence made her famous. Just weeks after returning to Colombia she joined 3 of her 4 sons as homicide victims.
Gustavo Gaviria was Pablo's first cousin and right hand man. His death at the hands of the extra-judicial "Search Block" prompted Pablo to wage war on the government
Jorge Luis Ochoa is possible the #1 importer of Coke into the United States ever. I calculated he oversaw the importation of 5 Billion grams... he only served 5 years in Colombian prison and is currently a very wealthy businessman living openly in Spain. He is Fabio Ochoa's brother.
Pablo was the face of Colombian crime, the most violent, if not the most important. His death provided the smokescreen for business as usual to continue. Prices for Coke actually reached there lowest point several years after his passing.
Roberto Escobar is the brother of Pablo, and succeeded Gustavo Gaviria as his right hand man and chief accountant. During his 10 year prison term he was blinded by a letter bomb sent into the prison. Today he attempts to enforce I.P. rights on his deceased brother, in 2016, for example he attempted to sue Netflix for $1 Billion dollars for their #Narcos series.
